<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-205-277 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 430 925</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  March 4 1991 v8 n9 p4(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SunAccount software ported to Ultrix systems; version 3.5 tosupport Oracle's SQL*Net. (Systems Union Inc.'s accountingsoftware) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Systems Union Inc announces the migration of its SunAccountaccounting software package to the Ultrix environment.andP;  In arelated announcement the firm unveiled SunAccount 3.5, a newversion of the software that features client/server support forOracle's SQL*Net.andP;  SunAccount, which currently supports VMS,MS-DOS and Unix variants from IBM, NCR, Mips Computer Systems andAltos Computer Systems, has the same look and feel when run onUltrix and is completely file compatible across all platforms.andO;Version 3.5 of the software includes pop-up query windows, amatrix report writer, encumbrance accounting capabilities and afixed assets module.andP;  Systems Union states that other releasessupporting virtually all major database platforms are forthcoming,enabling users to use SunAccount as a front end to relationalDBMSs.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Systems Union Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   SunAccount 3.5 (Accounting software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware MigrationFinancial Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SunAccount software ported to Ultrix systems; version 3.5 to support Oracle'sSQL*NetandM;NEW YORK -- Systmes Union is now shipping SunAccout, its accounting software,for Ultrix.andP;  The software was previously available for PCs and VMS-basedsystems as well as Unix systems from IBM, NCR, Mips Computer Systems andAltos Computer Systems.andM;&quot;Our product looks the same and feels the same on all of the platforms thatwe support, and the data files are compatible, [so] customers can move fromVMS to Ultrix without having to rekey data,&quot; said Systems Union CEO RobinMorris.andM;Systems Union also announced version 3.5 of SunAccout, which includesclient/server support for Oracle's SQL*Net.andP;  Users will be able to utilizeSunAccount as a front end to relational database management systems, Morrissaid.andM;&quot;Our direction is to be database-independent ultimately.andP;  We'll be releasingsupport for SQL*Net and Microsoft's SQL Server first, and are currentlyformulating plans for further releases on all major database platfors,&quot; hesaid.andM;Version 3.5 includes a matrix report writer, pop-up query windows,encumbrance accounting capabilities, a fixed assets module and documentdefinition.andM;The encumbrance accounting feature lets users run a check on the amount ofmoney about to be spent on an order.andP;  The fixed assets module supports anumber of new international requirements, Morris said.andM;The user document definition capability lets users define the format ofdocuments, Morris said.andM;&quot;An American company can now do business just about anywhere in the world andautomatically meet government requirements for asset reporting.andP;  andlsqb;Thismodule] also includes a multicurrency disposal feature,&quot; he said.andM;Systems Union will soon release a Kanji Chinese version of SunAccount, and isworking on Malaysian and Hungarian versions, German, Spanish, Portuguese andFrench versions are already available.andM;For additional information, Systems Union Inc. can be contacted at 244 E.andO;48th St., New York, NY 10017, (212) 753-7777.andO;</TEXT></DOC>